# Tailwind Canonical Utilities

- When a built-in Tailwind v4 utility expresses the same value, prefer the canonical class over `[]` (e.g. `min-w-180` not `min-w-[720px]`, `bg-linear-to-r` not `bg-gradient-to-r`).
- **IDE:** `suggestCanonicalClasses` is `ignore` in `.vscode/settings.json` — conventions live here and in `AGENTS.md`, not as editor warnings.
- **Do not edit** `src/lib/components/ui/**` for canonical sweeps — shadcn generated; folder excluded from Tailwind IntelliSense lint.

## Preferred

```svelte
<!-- good -->
<div class="max-h-75 w-30 shrink-0 bg-linear-to-r from-sky-400 to-indigo-400" />

<!-- avoid when equivalent utility exists -->
<div class="max-h-[300px] w-[120px] flex-shrink-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-sky-400 to-indigo-400" />
```

## Use `[]` Only When Needed

- Complex values: `max-h-[min(24rem,70vh)]`, `h-[calc(100vh-3.5rem)]`
- No scale token: `sm:max-w-[425px]` when `106.25` is not on the scale
- Third-party constraints: fixed widget heights
